# React Spectrum 2 Only

Use only React Spectrum 2 APIs and patterns for all new UI work.

## Requirements

- Do not create new components using Spectrum 1 packages, components, hooks, or styling APIs.
- Prefer the latest React Spectrum package set and usage patterns available in this repository.
- When touching existing Spectrum 1 code, migrate to Spectrum 2 instead of extending Spectrum 1 usage.
- Keep design-system imports consistent with Spectrum 2 across modified files.

## Review Checklist

- Any newly added Spectrum import must be from Spectrum 2 packages.
- No new references to deprecated or legacy Spectrum 1 APIs are introduced.
- Refactors and feature work should reduce (or at minimum not increase) Spectrum 1 surface area.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: adds/expands Spectrum 1 usage
import { Button } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: import from the Spectrum 2 package(s) this repo standardizes on
import { Button } from '<spectrum-2-package>';
```
